{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775865510159,"sessionID":"ses_2862ad894ffeO6j5ilO36o4JCz","part":{"id":"prt_d79d5390c0014p73yK6qu6KFG9","messageID":"msg_d79d533a7001L1XCTuhnXVRAts","sessionID":"ses_2862ad894ffeO6j5ilO36o4JCz","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865544813,"sessionID":"ses_2862ad894ffeO6j5ilO36o4JCz","part":{"id":"prt_d79d5481a001npDBLpzJ2iQ3X6","messageID":"msg_d79d533a7001L1XCTuhnXVRAts","sessionID":"ses_2862ad894ffeO6j5ilO36o4JCz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_9496973382c548ccae5a616d","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide a high-level Python client (`AgentRuntimeClient`) that enables users to invoke AgentRuntime workloads through the Router data plane with minimal boilerplate. The client abstracts session bootstrapping, HTTP lifecycle management, and timeout handling behind a simple `invoke()` API with context manager support.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` class in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - Constructor accepting `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n  - Context manager protocol (`__enter__` / `__exit__`)\n  - `invoke(payload, timeout)` — POST JSON to the invocation base URL with session header\n  - `close()` — release underlying `requests.Session`\n  - Auto-bootstrap of `session_id` via GET on the invocation base URL when not provided\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Low-level HTTP client with connection pooling\n  - `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET invocation URL, read `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n  - `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` — POST JSON with session header\n  - `close()` — close HTTP session\n- Public export of `AgentRuntimeClient` from `agentcube/__init__.py`\n- Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`) in `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n- Timeout defaults: read `120s`, connect `5.0s`, with per-call override support\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Control plane operations (session create/delete for AgentRuntime — handled separately)\n- Code Interpreter functionality (`CodeInterpreterClient`)\n- Authentication token management for data plane (Router handles JWT)\n- Retry logic, streaming responses, or async I/O\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files affected\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | New — `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | New — low-level data plane HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Modified — add `AgentRuntimeClient` to `__all__` |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | New — exception hierarchy |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Existing — `create_session` reused |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Existing — `get_logger` reused |\n| `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` | New — usage example |\n| `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | New — unit/integration tests |\n| `pyproject.toml` | No change — dependencies already cover `requests` |\n\n### Dependencies\n\nNo new external dependencies. Uses existing `requests` library and shared utilities (`create_session`, `get_logger`).\n\n### Backward compatibility\n\n- Additive change only — no existing APIs are modified\n- `agentcube/__init__.py` gains a new export; existing `CodeInterpreterClient` import path unchanged\n- `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` gains `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` export\n\n### Operational impact\n\n- Router must expose `GET /v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` for session bootstrapping\n- Router must accept `POST` to the same path with JSON body and `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- No server-side changes required beyond existing Router contract\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Unified client for Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime\n\n**Approach:** Single `AgentCubeClient` class with mode selection (code-interpreter vs agent-runtime).\n\n**Rejected because:**\n- The two workflows have fundamentally different lifecycles (session create/delete vs session bootstrap via GET)\n- Different error semantics and retry requirements\n- Would create a god class with divergent method sets\n- Users typically use one or the other, not both simultaneously\n\n### 2. Async-first client using `aiohttp` or `httpx`\n\n**Approach:** Build the SDK around async I/O from the start.\n\n**Rejected because:**\n- The existing `CodeInterpreterClient` uses synchronous `requests`; mixing sync/async would create inconsistency\n- Target users (data scientists, ML engineers) predominantly work in synchronous Jupyter/notebook contexts\n- Can be added as a future `agentcube-async` package without breaking this design\n\n### 3. Session ID as required constructor argument\n\n**Approach:** Require users to always provide `session_id` explicitly, removing auto-bootstrap.\n\n**Rejected because:**\n- Adds friction for the common case where users just want to invoke an agent\n- The Router already supports bootstrapping via GET; not using it wastes a built-in capability\n- Current design supports both explicit reuse (pass `session_id`) and auto-bootstrap (omit it)\n\n### 4. Configuration dataclass\n\n**Approach:** Introduce a `Configuration` dataclass to centralize defaults and environment variable resolution.\n\n**Rejected because:**\n- Existing codebase pattern distributes config resolution across constructors (see `CodeInterpreterClient`)\n- Would require refactoring existing clients for consistency\n- Adds indirection without clear benefit for the current number of configuration parameters\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### Session bootstrapping strategy\n\n`AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps `session_id` in `__init__` by calling `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`, which performs a GET request to the invocation base URL and reads the `x-agentcube-session-id` response header. If the header is missing, raises `ValueError`.\n\n**Rationale:** Eager bootstrapping fails fast rather than deferring errors to the first `invoke()` call.\n\n### Timeout handling\n\n- Constructor accepts `timeout` (read, default 120s) and `connect_timeout` (default 5.0s)\n- Per-call `invoke(timeout)` overrides the read timeout\n- Effective timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, effective_read_timeout)`\n\n**Rationale:** Matches the pattern established by `CodeInterpreterClient` and `ControlPlaneClient` for consistency.\n\n### Header naming\n\nSession header uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` (defined as class constant `SESSION_HEADER` on `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`).\n\n**Rationale:** `requests` library normalizes headers to lowercase; using lowercase consistently avoids case-sensitivity bugs.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n| Test | Coverage |\n|------|----------|\n| Constructor with explicit `session_id` | No bootstrap call |\n| Constructor without `session_id` | Bootstrap GET called, header parsed |\n| Bootstrap missing header | `ValueError` raised |\n| `invoke` with valid payload | POST with correct headers and body |\n| `invoke` without session | `ValueError` raised |\n| `invoke` with custom timeout | Timeout tuple passed to request |\n| Context manager exit | `close()` called, session released |\n| Exception hierarchy | `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError` defined |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775865544805,"end":1775865544812}}}}
